data.enText: to put people or things into groups according to what type they are
Participants were categorized according to age.

data.chText: 他最近的作品既不属于小说也不属于自传。
data.enText: His latest work cannot be categorized as either a novel or an autobiography.

tr: place into or assign to a category
example: Children learn early on to categorize

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, also use 英国英语亦用 categorise

value.def: If you categorize people or things, you divide them into sets or you say which set they belong to.

example.ex: Lindsay, like his films, is hard to categorise...
example.tran: 林赛这个人和他的电影一样，很难归类。

example.ex: Make a list of your child's toys and then categorise them as sociable or antisocial.
example.tran: 把孩子的玩具列个单子，然后将其分为交际型和非交际型两类。

example.ex: Her first novel defies easy categorisation.
example.tran: 她的第一部小说很难归类。

example.ex: ...the categorisation of new types of missiles.
